5.2. Troubleshooting
V pripade problemu se zapnutim AutoTLS funkcionality, zkontrolujeme nasledujici logy na CM serveru:

cloudera-scm-server logy - /var/log/cloudera-scm-server/cloudera-scm-server.log
certmanager logy - /var/log/cloudera-scm-agent/certmanager.log
a certifikaty ve slozce /opt/cloudera

delete sudoers


# Check certificate for correct DNS alias
openssl x509 -in certificate.crt -text -noout

# Check if certificate matches key
openssl pkey -in /opt/cloudera/AutoTLS/keys/${hostname}.key -pubout -outform pem | sha256sum
openssl x509 -in /opt/cloudera/AutoTLS/certs/${hostname}.crt -pubkey -noout -outform pem | sha256sum

#or
openssl x509 -noout -modulus -in your_certificate.crt | openssl md5
openssl rsa -noout -modulus -in your_private_key.key | openssl md5


6. Nahrazeni certifikatu
Pote co obdrzime podepsany certifikat, je treba ho nahrat na Cloudera Manager server do slozky /opt/cloudera/AutoTLS/certs. Dale take musime nahrat jeho privatni klic do slozky /opt/cloudera/AutoTLS/keys.

Certifikat se musi jmenovat ${hostname}.crt

Klic se musi jmenovat ${hostname}.key

Pote, co budeme mit toto pripravene, muzeme spustit ansible skript pro vytvoreni potrebnych keystoru a pem souboru a nasledne je rozdistribuovat na servery, kde certifikaty nahrajeme.



# Clone ansible repo
git clone https://git.kb.cz/scm/cotool/ansible.git
cd ansible/auto_tls

# Edit vars file and write password in cm_admin_password and optionaly switch cm_admin_user to your personal user
vi roles/replace_certificates/vars/main.yaml

# Replace certificates in cluster
ansible-playbook playbooks/replace_certificates.yaml -i inventory/cdpd -b -u $(logname) --ask-pass

# Replace certificates on worker nodes only
ansible-playbook playbooks/replace_certificates.yaml -i inventory/cdpd -b -u $(logname) --ask-pass -l worker





7. Adhoc prikazy


# Check CSR
openssl req -text -noout -verify -in CSR.csr

# Check certificate 
openssl x509 -in certificate.crt -text -noout

# Check key
openssl rsa -in privateKey.key -check

# Check p12 
openssl pkcs12 -info -in keyStore.p12

# Convert JKS to Pem
## convert to p12 first
keytool -importkeystore -srckeystore cm-auto-global_truststore.jks -destkeystore keystore.p12 -srcstoretype jks -deststoretype pkcs12
## Convert p12 to pem
openssl pkcs12 -in keystore.p12 -out keystore.pem
